
[1]perfume

   PERFU'ME, n. [L. per and fumus, smoke, or fumo, to fumigate.]

   1. A substance that emits a scent or odor which affects agreeably the
   organs of smelling, as musk, civet, spices or aromatics of any kind; or
   any composition of aromatic substances.

   2. The scent, odor or volatile particles emitted from sweet smelling
   substances.

   No rich perfumes refresh the fruitful field.

    PERFU'ME, v.t. To scent; to fill or impregnate with a grateful odor;
             as, to perfume an apartment; to perfume a garment.

   And Carmel's flower top perfumes the skies.
